NFS VOLUME ---an external server not part of your cluster but needed to connect NFS volume to your k8s database pod
Steps in configuring NFS server on AWS
create an ubuntu server on AWS
•	Sudo apt-get update
•	Sudo apt install nfs-kernel-server -y
•	Create the export directory
o	Sudo mkdir -p /mnt/share/
•	We want all clients access to the directory so we will remove restrictive permissions
o	Sudo chown nobody:nogroup /mnt/share/
o	Sudo chmod 777 /mnt/share/
•	Assign server access to clients through NFS export file
o	Sudo vi /etc/exports
o	Add /mnt/share/ *(rw,sync,no_subtree_check,no_root_squash)
o	Save and quit
•	Export the shared directory
o	Sudo exportfs -a
o	Sudo systemctl restart nfs-kernel-server
•	Open firewall for client on port 2049
o	Open port on security group in AWS
•	Configure the client machine by installing NFS common on all your nodes
o	Sudo apt-get update -y && sudo apt-get install nfs-common -y
o	Sudo apt-get install nfs-common

